  "title": "Quality Operations Specialist, Central Kitchen",
  "description": "<p>1. Perform daily periodic checks of Central Kitchen to ensure compliance to in-house GMP/GHP standards, SOP, Product Specifications, etc.<br>\n<br>\n2. Conduct random checks on incoming raw materials, and perform product cutting on raw materials to ensure goods received are within in-house specifications.<br>\n<br>\n3. Ensure Process Verification and Validation exercise are completed (i.e. SOP/CCP verification, new product launch process observation, monthly facility checks, monthly traceability exercise, finished goods shelf-life verification, etc.)<br>\n<br>\n4. Conduct investigations on product/process non-conformance (on-line and customer complaints) and follow-up on proposed corrective/preventive measures to ensure effectiveness.<br>\n<br>\n5. Promptly follow-up with contractors (chemical/pest control) during routine servicing to ensure work orders are conducted as per contract.<br>\n<br>\n6. Participate and engage in quality system implementation (audit activities by regulatory/certification bodies and customers).<br>\n<br>\n7. Conduct data/trend analysis on non-conformity of raw material/finished goods, pest reporting statistics, monthly production and facility check statistics, etc. for process and quality improvement.<br>\n<br>\n8. Ensure analysis of food products via microbiological and physical testing, calibration of lab equipment and measurement tools, internal sensory evaluation are conducted as per schedule.<br>\n<br>\n9. Report all non-conformances, discrepancies and/or deviations, and follow-up on the investigation of the non-conformity results.<br>\n<br>\n10. Other projects as assigned.<br>\n<br>\n</p>",
